[[File:Crystal key detail.png|left|150px]]
The '''crystal key''' is created by combining a [[tooth half of key]] with a [[loop half of key]], displaying the message, "''You join the two halves of the key together.''" Key halves can be obtained as rewards from [[Barrows]], the [[Gnome Restaurant]] [[Minigames|minigame]], [[Managing Miscellania]], [[Treasure Trails]], looting [[magpie impling]]s, [[random events]], the [[rare drop table]], spoils of war, etc.

It is used to open the [[crystal chest]] located inside a house in [[Taverley]]. The chest always contains an [[uncut dragonstone]] in addition to a variety of other items. Some items of note are 3 [[runite bar]]s, [[rune platelegs]]/[[Rune plateskirt|plateskirt]] (depending on the player's gender), or another half of the crystal key. After the key is used, it disappears and the player must use another one if they want to open the chest again.

The crystal key may not be placed on the [[steel key ring]], as it is non-reusable.

The crystal key can be upgraded to an [[enhanced crystal key]] at a [[singing bowl]] in [[Prifddinas]], for the cost of 10 [[crystal shard]]s.

